# IX Popover rules

Popovers live at z-20 with no scrim. They are for **quick, non-destructive** inline actions.

## Use `IxQuickPopover`, not raw `Popover`

`@procore/core-react` `Popover` hardcodes `arrow: true` — the arrow/tail is non-IX-compliant for our toolbar patterns. Compose via:

- `IxQuickPopover` — `src/components/templates/ix-popover/IxQuickPopover.tsx` (wraps `OverlayTrigger` + `Popover.Content` with `arrow={false}`).
- `IxPopoverTriggerButton` — consistent secondary-button trigger.
- `ConfigurationPopoverContent` — toggle-list body used for Filter / Configure toolbar patterns.
- **`FormulatorFilterPopoverContent`** — richer filter bodies built with `@procore/json-formulator` (`Form` + Clear All / Apply). Use with `FilterToolbarPopoverButton` and popover **`width` ~360px** for readable field layout.
- **`ColumnConfigurePopoverContent`** — column visibility, pragmatic-drag-and-drop reorder, and row density; use with `ConfigureToolbarPopoverButton` and **`width` ~320px**.

Keep the **AG Grid sidebar** (filters / columns panels) available for power users when you ship Smart Grid filter/configure popovers.

Canonical examples in this scaffold:

- [`popovers/PopoverComponentFilter.tsx`](src/components/templates/popovers/PopoverComponentFilter.tsx) — "Filter" toolbar button that opens a checklist.
- [`popovers/PopoverComponentConfigure.tsx`](src/components/templates/popovers/PopoverComponentConfigure.tsx) — "Configure" toolbar button with the same pattern.

A long-term core-react proposal (`Popover` accepts `arrow?: boolean`) is filed in `TOOLINATOR-EXTENSIONS.md`.

## Hard rules

- NEVER use for **destructive** actions (delete, void, approve-with-impact). Use a `Modal` (z-50).
- NEVER contain **form-level Save** (whole-form commit). Popovers are single-field or single-toggle commits at most.
- NEVER trigger from a **link** — only from a button or pressable.
- NEVER place **inside a Modal** as the trigger context.
- NEVER **nest** popovers. Avoid complex editors (rich text) inside.

## Size and content

- Content must be **scannable** — 2–3 scrolls of content at most.
- **Max size: 50%** of the region the trigger lives in. Use `portalContainer` on `IxQuickPopover` set to that region for true "50% of region" sizing.
- **Single-column** only. No tabs or sub-navigation.
- Must be completable in **seconds**.

## Vibe check

If the user loses meaningful work by accidentally clicking the background, it should NOT be a popover. Use a Slide-Out (Tearsheet) instead.

